text: I became a fan of seventeen back in 2017 after listening to the 13 member ver of this song. it was a huge hit in my friend circle and its almost 6 years since then. i lost interest in kpop around 2021 due to exams and college and now I'm back and I cant even tell you how proud I am to see them so successful. like I used to watch all their videos back then and thought how underrated they were and when they gained popularity with going seventeen I could see that people found their worth but I had to let go of them little to make my life easier. it didnt help, but now I learned to balance with my life and enjoy fangirling over them. not even lying these guys make me so happy. i feel like a proud mother. brb imma cry in a corner

author: @letuan6465
text:
당신은 따라야합니다. 모두 공유하세요. 신을 믿으십시오. 부처를 믿으십시오. 자선을 위해 열심히 일하고, 생명을 풀어주고,기도하십시오.
열심히 공부한다 / 열심히 일한다 / 경제 발전을 위해 열심히 일한다 / 질병 예방을 위해 열심히 일한다 / 모두를 치료하기 위해 열심히 일한다 / 도움이 필요한 사람들을 돕기 위해 열심히 일한다.
자녀에게주의 깊게 가르치십시오. 자녀에게 윤리적으로 살도록 가르치십시오. 자녀에게 법에 따라 살도록 가르치십시오. 아이들에게 술을 마시지 말고 마약을 사용하지 말며 도박을하지 말라고 가르치십시오.
어린이들에게 TV 시청 시간을 줄 이도록 조언하십시오. 휴대 전화를 보는 시간을 줄여야합니다. 공부하고, 일하고, 스포츠를하고, 자녀에게 모범을 보이는 데 집중하십시오. 검소하게 살고 장난 치지 말고 다른 사람을 사랑해야하고 조금 영리하게 사십시오.
열심히 공부하고, 돈을 벌고, 도움이 필요한 사람들을 돕고, 질병을 예방하고, 모두를 치료해야합니다. 술을 마시거나, 맥주를 마시거나, 마약을 사용하지 않아야합니다.
슬프다면 부처님의 가르침을 지켜보고 따르십시오.
동물의 생명을 구하고 / 사람에게 친절하게 / 사람에게 해를 끼치 지 않으며 / 거짓말하지 마십시오.
인생의 모든 것을 사랑하십시오. "Namo Amitabha Buddha"를 읽고 암송하십시오.
부처님의 충고에 따라 생활하고 모든 사람과 좋은 것을 나누십시오. 나쁜 것을 공유하거나 퍼 뜨리지 마십시오. 당신은 선과 권리를 전파해야합니다. 다른 사람을 존중해야합니다.
조화롭게 생활하십시오. 낙태하지 마십시오. 간음하지 말고 어른의 말을 들어야합니다. 국가 전통에 따라 생활하십시오. 우리 조상의 전통에 따라 생활하십시오.
아픈 사람을 돕고, 아픈 사람을 돕고, 아픈 사람이 아플 때 약을 먹어야합니다. 자선을 위해 열심히 일하면서 동물을 풀어주는 것은 그들에게 자유롭게 살 수있는 기회를줍니다.
가난한 사람들이 음식을 먹고, 가난한 사람들이 치료를 받도록, 가난한 사람들이 학교에 가고, 가난한 사람들이 머물 곳을 갖도록 돕기 위해 돈을 기부하십시오.
가난한 사람들이 더 나은 삶을 살도록 도와주세요. 모든 사람들이 따뜻하게 먹고 옷을 입히고 따뜻하고 시원하고 행복한 삶을 영원하도록 돕고 사람들이 영원히 행복하고 번영하는 삶을 살도록 돕습니다. 검소하게 살아야하고, 겸손하게 살고, 정직하게 살고, 다른 사람을 존중하며, 평등하게 살고, 서로에게 양보해야합니다. 모두를 사랑하십시오.
조상 숭배. 조상의 무덤을 부지런히 방문하고 향을 피우십시오. 세상의 모든 사람들이 행복하고 번영하는 삶을 살 수 있도록 도와주세요. 사람들이 학교에 갈 수 있도록 도와주세요
부처님을 숭배하기 위해 정기적으로 사원에 가야합니다. 사려 깊은 작업을 처리하기 위해 휴식을 취하고 건강을 유지하십시오. 자선에 관대해야합니다. 모든 중생을 사랑해야합니다
예배, 헌금, 신 부처를 기증합니다. 숭배, 헌금, 보살을 기증합니다. 숭배, 헌금, 거룩한 신을 기증합니다.
조상 숭배.불교 선전.
다음을 모두 숭배하십시오 : 신 , 성자 , 요정 , 부처님 , 보살 ,신 신,신 부처,하늘과 부처

text:
3:04 I NEED TO KNOW WHO THAT IS!!

this is the first time I've watched anything with them and I liked the video and all but that part..... Made me cry and chills ran through my body. It was breathtaking and I need to know who made that impact on me with that stare that made me forget my own name

Edit: OK so far I know his name is Jun?? I watched a live performance of this song and people timestamped this part and said stuff like "Ahh Jun's part so amazing! He's so good looking" and stuff like that. Wow. I need to know more!

author: @LinnSobi
text:
This is the first video of Seventeen I've ever watched. I've never seen ANYTHING with them at all before. I'm a massive BTS fan so I've heard the name of their band a few times, but never really felt like looking into them yet.
But I was watching Roomie's video and this song played a few seconds and I liked what I heard, so here I am.

Already a few seconds in I started smiling widely and enjoyed what I watching. Really good! And honestly at 3:04 cried. I literally gaped and was caught of guard how much I liked that part. I had to pause and cry for a few moments and then replay that small part of the bridge over and over again. I NEED to know who that was, who was singing that part. His eyes looked into my soul and everything about it made my head spin. Amazing... Wow.

So please let me know more videos I should check out from them! I literally have no idea where to start😅

Edit: OK so far I know his name is Jun?? I watched a live performance of this song and people timestamped this part and said stuff like "Ahh Jun's part so amazing! He's so good looking" and stuff like that. Wow. I need to know more!

author: @ClaireXue
text:
THEORY:

When they say "I'm like a bird not a turkey" means that they are free spirited, graceful, and they fly. Just like how a bird flies up and down, they have their ups and downs, but in the end they fly. Just like a bird. Not a turkey as a turkey is not graceful, they gobble like crazy maniacs, and they can't fly. It's easy to kill turkeys to make a yummy thanksgiving meal, whereas you shouldn't kill birds for food. I'm talking about graceful birds.
Then after a few words, they say "In the air!" Which indicates that they are very successful and soar in the air. Unlike a turkey, ugh.

author: @ScribblerinPanic
text:
my fave unit is still not failing me... :)

hoshi - whatever this boy do is marvelous to me. i just can't fathom how his brain works for creating complex choreos and being able to teach it to either 3 or 12 members. and when all is well and done, he'll turn into a childish, noisy, crazy soonyoung. really fascinating...
dino - seriously, puberty is extra good to this boy. he's getting better and better looking as he turns to an adult. and not just physically, his talent for dancing, rapping, and singing are improving so much too. one day, this boy will surprise a lot of us...
jun - super glad he is getting more and more song lines. he deserves it, his voice has a certain allure to it. it's not strong as that of wonwoo or high as that of dk and sk but it's soothing...
the8 - i have said this is a different video but if hoshi's the god of dance, the8 is the king. enough said... :)

Seventeen is the first kpop group I've really started getting into where everyone seems to be able to do everything. Most of them sing, every single one of them is amazing at dancing and I don't know much about members not in the rap unit rapping, apart from Dino haha. Also, they're all so young! Dino is born the year after me, and I believe I'm in the same year as Vernon. It's crazy how talented they all are at such a young age.

author: @reinuta
text: This is coming from someone who only vaguely follows SVT whenever they have a comeback and knows very little about the members besides a handful of their names and the division into different units; I've liked all of their title songs and thought BOOMBOOM was a catchy title for all ot13. When I finally decided to check this song out after seeing it in circulation, I was shocked by how GOOD it was and how it felt like it was on a different level musically from their other tracks I've heard. I was even more SHOCKED to find out this was the Performance Unit's song, because the quality feels as if it is a Vocal Unit track (vocally, song arrangement, feel of maturity). It led me to check out the entire album, and for me it's the best song by a landslide. I guess what I'm trying to say is, I know some people crap on the Performance Unit, but they put out the BEST track on this album, and this is from a non-stan (although I think this song has definitely turned me into a fan).

author: @tangerine3968
text:
Okay, since nobody is going to spazz and talk about my baby Minghao, I'll do it on my own:

First off: MINGHAO DAMN SON YOU'RE UPGRADING REAL FAST. You have sooooo many lines and soooo many shots of you and, really, there's no need to question your dancing skills because you've always been a really gifted dancer. YOU'RE SIZZLING HOT, BABY. I'M SO PROUD!!!

Second: MINGHAO'S DIRTY BLONDE HAIR PRETTY MUCH CONFIRMED HIS HIDDEN SLYTHERIN-DRACO MALFOY VIBES. THE STRIPED DARK SUIT, THE BROOCH ON HIS CHEST, THEM EAR PIERCINGS, THE NECKTIE, THE BLACK RIPPED JEANS, THE SLEEK BLACK SHOES. EVEN ON HIS SOLO SHOTS THE ROLLED-UP SLEEVES DID JUSTICE TO HIS SLYTHERIN VIBE. EVERYTHING ABOUT HIS LOOK EMPHASIZED THE SLYTHERIN-NESS I'VE ALWAYS SEEN IN MINGHAO YAS YAS YAS.

Third: MINGHAO HAS SO MUCH LINES OMFGGGGGG I saw a decent line distribution video of this MV and it seems that Minghao was the one who sung the autotuned parts in all 3 choruses and I'm convinced because he was the only one out of the boys who lipsynced to those autotuned parts ;u;

Fourth: DID YOU SEE MINGHAO'S SLIGHT B-BOYING MOVES AT 3:18??? AND HIS MULTIPLE SPIN AT 2:18??? Those parts were so dang COOL, they're so Minghao and they suit the MV so much, I'm so pprrrooouuudd!

Fifth: I LIVE FOR MINGHAO'S SOLO SHOTS IN THIS MV. HE'S JUST SO HOT, I CANNOT DEAL. The "I'm like a bird" part with the wings were dramatic af but daaaamn Minghao, my love, YOU DID GREAT! YOU'RE THE HOTTEST!

And finally, I'm just so so so so so proud of the whole Performance Unit! This song is my ultimate fave from Going Seventeen album and my ultimate fave out of all Performance Unit songs, and I'm so happy Highlight is Performance Unit's song! The whole MV suits the boys so much, it suits the hype of the song so much, it's such a lovely lovely New Year present for the fans (especially Minghao fans like me ehehe). I hope this MV will receive the hype it deserves because Performance Unit should not be slept on! 
These talented boys should not be slept on, guys!!!!!

author: @kwonspo7839
text:
to anyone who's wondering why there's only 4 members here when SEVENTEEN has 13 members..... this one's for you.

*SEVENTEEN* is made up of 3 units: vocal team, hiphop team and performance team.

*HIGHLIGHT* is one of the songs from their Going Seventeen mini album which is sang by the performance team: *Jun, Hoshi, The8 and Dino*. the performance unit is in charge of the choreographies for SEVENTEEN's songs.

member timestamps (according to age):

0:13 - Wen Junhui, or *JUN* (96 liner, China line)
0:41 - Kwon Soonyoung, or *HOSHI* (leader of performance team unit, 96 liner, choreographer)
2:14 - Xu Minghao, or *THE8* (97 liner, China line)
1:33 - Lee Chan, or *DINO* (99 liner, maknae of SEVENTEEN)

text:
This concept is AMAZING I've never seen ANYTHING like it before! 

The outfits remind me of blood sweat and tears, the stage reminds me of NCT, the stage also reminds me of Taeyeon WHY dance performance video, the photos and videos behind them remind me of I NEED U, the song kinda reminds me of BTS WINGS (the song not the album), but it also has a seventeen dubstep spin on it(I like this song even better!), and the dancing and choreography is incredible! 

It's so hard to be original these days where almost everything has been done before, but they have managed to come up with something I've never seen before!! A ROUND OF APPLAUSE!! I'm so proud! 😭😭👌🏻💖💖💖

author: @Jaden3459
text:
Before I get into my comment, IS HOSHI GIVING ANYONE ELSE MAJOR TAEMIN VIBES?! I can't breathe!!! 

But anyway, I love my Hoshi (bias) and I think his choreos are brilliant but I don't think a lot of people realize from an unbiased perspective that Jun is probably the best dancer/performer in SVT. He brings an edge that the others have yet to replicate, it's really amazing to watch him go,  with this super confident, dramatic flair and every move is almost flawless in it's delivery. It doesn't hurt that his voice is amazing, which i'm really only noticing today, and he looks like a freaking statue. As our Hoshi said, it's really hard to pull off blue hair lol. If that wasn't enough he came out of nowhere rapping with this deep-ass voice?! Oh and he's a good actor? Does Pledis know they have an all-kill gem here? I might have to reconsider his ranking on my list, I hope he gets more popular.

author: @TheCupcakeCup
text: I love how SEVENTEEN always HIGHLIGHTs their members with a particular song or performances. It shows how much they want EVERYONE to be able to shine and NOT JUST CERTAIN MEMBERS. In EVERY ALBUM they always have one song specifically for each unit and it makes everything fair. I also notices that when they does special stages, they always gives most lines to the members that have less lines in their promoting title tracks. Like recently Jun and The8 sings most in Show Me Your Love. I love how they manage their group and I hope due to this unselfishness, they will last a long time. Anyways, HAPPY NEW YEAR SEVENTEEN AND CARATS! I LOVE YOU GUYS AND LETS CONTINUE SUPPORTING OUR SEBONGIES~ <3
